---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Exclusive Interviews | Scripture Alive Insights"
  description="Tune into enlightening interviews that offer a deeper understanding of Scripture."
  type="media"
  ogImage="https://assets.spiritmediapublishing.com/scripture-alive/d0b2aceb029909de1f63dd05cb63c4af_1200_80-rdodoupx7nidwtzgvi31qpkih69etmmxm500ypsw76.webp"
>

  <!-- Page Heading -->
  <section class="py-10 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-primary font-serif">
        Check Out Jeremy Kluth's Podcast/Radio Interviews
      </h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bio Section -->
  <section class="pb-8 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded p-6 bg-white shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 items-start">
          <!-- Bio Image -->
          <div class="flex-shrink-0">
            <img
              src="https://assets.spiritmediapublishing.com/scripture-alive/d0b2aceb029909de1f63dd05cb63c4af_1200_80-rdodoupx7nidwtzgvi31qpkih69etmmxm500ypsw76.webp"
              alt="Jeremy Kluth"
              title="Jeremy Kluth"
              loading="lazy"
              class="rounded shadow-md"
              style="width: 160px;"
            />
          </div>
          <!-- Bio Text -->
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary font-serif">Jeremy Kluth</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
              Jeremy Kluth is the Founder of Scripture Alive, a ministry that seeks to engage people with the Word of Truth to impact real lives. His unique and memorable dramatic Scripture presentations include whole chapters and stories from 20 different books of the Bible. These serve to highlight the heroes of the faith and God's redemptive plan through them like David, Elijah, Daniel, Peter, John, Paul and a One-Man Passion Play covering the Triumphal Entry through the Resurrection.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
              Jeremy is a passionate lover of God and His Word and that is displayed through his various podcast/radio interviews where he shares his personal story of what got him into Scripture memory along with sharing anecdotes of his book on Scripture memory and techniques that anyone can use to more effectively memorize Scripture. See below for some of his interviews which include being a guest on Moody Radio, Generations Radio, the Scripture Memory Podcast, and more.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Interview 1: Scripture Memory Podcast - POWER System (YouTube embed) -->
  <section class="py-8 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-start">
        <!-- Video Embed -->
        <div class="w-full md:w-5/12 flex-shrink-0">
          <div class="relative w-full" style="padding-top: 56.25%;">
            <iframe
              class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full rounded shadow-md"
              src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/e79dXsKfhK8"
              title="The Scripture Memory Podcast: The POWER System for Memorizing"
              frameborder="0"
              allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
              allowfullscreen
            ></iframe>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- Description -->
        <div class="w-full md:w-7/12 space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary font-serif">
            <a
              href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=e79dXsKfhK8"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              class="hover:text-accent transition-colors"
            >
              The Scripture Memory Podcast: The POWER System for Memorizing
            </a>
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            In this episode, Jeremy Kluth of Scripture Alive will join us again. He will introduce a new strategy for memorizing Scripture called The POWER System. Whether you are a veteran memorizer or just getting started, you'll want to tune in to learn this new method.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Interview 2: Moody Radio Quad Cities -->
  <section class="py-8 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-start">
        <!-- Image -->
        <div class="w-full md:w-5/12 flex-shrink-0">
          <a href="https://www.moodyradio.org/radioplayer.aspx?episode=539622&hour=1" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            <img
              src="https://assets.spiritmediapublishing.com/scripture-alive/b935343b78a571e3a47c0bcf57790708_1200_80-1024x576.webp"
              alt="Moody Radio Quad Cities: Scripture Alive - A Conversation with Jeremy Kluth"
              loading="lazy"
              width="800"
              height="450"
              class="w-full rounded shadow-md hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity"
            />
          </a>
        </div>
        <!-- Description -->
        <div class="w-full md:w-7/12 space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary font-serif">
            <a
              href="https://www.moodyradio.org/radioplayer.aspx?episode=539622&hour=1"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              class="hover:text-accent transition-colors"
            >
              Moody Radio Quad Cities: Scripture Alive - A Conversation with Jeremy Kluth
            </a>
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Is Scripture memory part of your discipleship plan? Why is it important to hide God's Word in our hearts? Jeremy Kluth, the founder of Scripture Alive, will be talking about his journey of Bible memory on Monday's show. Jeremy will share how he has combined this passion with drama, taking his presentations to 25 different countries. We'll also pick up some Bible memory tips and hear how memorizing God's Word is powerful and fruitful in our lives.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Interview 3: Generations Radio -->
  <section class="py-8 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-start">
        <!-- Image -->
        <div class="w-full md:w-5/12 flex-shrink-0">
          <a href="https://generations.org/tabs/search/podcasts/41186/episodes/2855" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            <img
              src="https://assets.spiritmediapublishing.com/scripture-alive/b935343b78a571e3a47c0bcf57790708_1200_80-1024x576.webp"
              alt="Generations Radio: The Power of Scripture Memory"
              loading="lazy"
              width="800"
              height="450"
              class="w-full rounded shadow-md hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity"
            />
          </a>
        </div>
        <!-- Description -->
        <div class="w-full md:w-7/12 space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary font-serif">
            <a
              href="https://generations.org/tabs/search/podcasts/41186/episodes/2855"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              class="hover:text-accent transition-colors"
            >
              Generations Radio: The Power of Scripture Memory
            </a>
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            The Psalm 1 picture of the godly man involves a meditation on the law of God day and night. This is especially important in a day like ours in which there is little time and resources dedicated to what a godly man does. Jeremy Kluth has dedicated his life to memorizing Scripture and encouraging others to the same thing. How do we assist our families in memorization? Here are a variety of creative, helpful hints for this extremely important element of family discipleship in the Word of God.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Interview 4: Scripture Memory Podcast - Your Motivation for Memorizing -->
  <section class="py-8 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-start">
        <!-- Video Embed -->
        <div class="w-full md:w-5/12 flex-shrink-0">
          <div class="relative w-full" style="padding-top: 56.25%;">
            <iframe
              class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full rounded shadow-md"
              src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/sk4_-Xffh6E"
              title="The Scripture Memory Podcast: Your Motivation for Memorizing"
              frameborder="0"
              allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
              allowfullscreen
            ></iframe>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- Description -->
        <div class="w-full md:w-7/12 space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary font-serif">
            <a
              href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sk4_-Xffh6E"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              class="hover:text-accent transition-colors"
            >
              The Scripture Memory Podcast: Your Motivation for Memorizing
            </a>
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            What motivates you to memorize? Is it the applause of man? Do you think you are being "super spiritual" in the pursuit of this discipline? Or perhaps, at this point in your journey, you are weary and have forgotten your motivation for hiding God's Word in your heart. In this episode, Jeremy Kluth, founder of Scripture Alive, will join us to discuss the important topic. He'll share with our hosts his original inspiration for memorizing and how to continue to discover new motivations for memorizing the Word of God.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Interview 5: Bible Memory Goal - Bible Character Memorization -->
  <section class="py-8 px-4 mb-8">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-start">
        <!-- Image -->
        <div class="w-full md:w-5/12 flex-shrink-0">
          <img
            src="https://assets.spiritmediapublishing.com/scripture-alive/b935343b78a571e3a47c0bcf57790708_1200_80-1024x576.webp"
            alt="Bible Memory Goal: What is Bible Character Memorization?"
            loading="lazy"
            width="800"
            height="450"
            class="w-full rounded shadow-md"
          />
        </div>
        <!-- Description -->
        <div class="w-full md:w-7/12 space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary font-serif">
            <a
              href="#"
              class="hover:text-accent transition-colors"
            >
              Bible Memory Goal: What is Bible Character Memorization?
            </a>
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Jeremy Kluth, the founder of Scripture Alive Ministry, shares this Bible memory technique that I honestly have never heard of before called character memorization. Learn about this interestingly new technique and find out whether or not it will work for you.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>